	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, what's up with all these enchanters? Yes ac is nice, and resists are nice... but "oh i'm an enchanter, ac would be nice cuz when i need to mez and stuff i get beat down on". None of you enchanters notice this drops in ToV? It's called 25ac over the usual 12 ac robe doesn't mean diddly squat (/agree bikkin). I.E. You're a level 55 enchanter tashing in ToV... it's not the 25 ac that'll keep you from dying as clerics and druids are racing to keep you alive, it's the aego that's keeping you alive with the hp buff. You can't mez anything in here and when it decides to claw you, you're pretty much dead unless your healers are on the ball. This robe is resist gear, that's pretty much it unless your tanking a vis ghoul knight in lguk and you're level 60. Just my 2 cents.<br><br>Hally<br>56 defiler<br>fennin<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
